research_municipality_step.notes: Austin, TX operates under a council-manager form of government. The Mayor is elected at-large, and ten Council Members are elected from single-member districts. Vanessa Fuentes was elected Mayor Pro Tem on January 6, 2025. Krista Laine unseated Mackenzie Kelly in District 6, and Marc Duchen won District 10 in the November 2024 elections. Mike Siegel is listed as the current Council Member for District 7.
